    "instructions": [
        "Prepare all ingredients: chop vegetables, measure sauces, and beat the eggs.",
        "In a small bowl, mix the soy sauce, oyster sauce, hoisin sauce, Worcestershire sauce, and sriracha. Set aside.",
        "Heat 1 tbsp of oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add the beaten eggs and scramble until just set. Remove from the pan and set aside.",
        "Add another tablespoon of oil to the pan. Sauté the yellow onion, carrots, and bell pepper for 3–4 minutes until beginning to soften.",
        "Add the shallots, garlic, and ginger. Stir-fry for about 1 minute until fragrant.",
        "Add the cooked pork and stir-fry for 2–3 minutes until heated through.",
        "Add the rice, breaking up any clumps, and stir everything together. Let the rice sit undisturbed for 1–2 minutes to get some crispy bits.",
        "Pour in the sauce mixture and stir until the rice and pork are evenly coated.",
        "Fold the scrambled eggs back in and mix well.",
        "Remove from heat and stir in chopped cilantro. Drizzle with sesame oil if using.",
        "Top with toasted sesame seeds and chopped peanuts before serving."
